to end her relationship</i>

15
00:00:37,108 --> 00:00:38,810
<i>with detective Vance.</i>

16
00:00:38,855 --> 00:00:41,852
You know, Bree, I would
have done anything for you.

17
00:00:44,518 --> 00:00:47,892
You have made a very big mistake.

18
00:00:56,157 --> 00:00:58,979
<i>It's often said that children learn</i>

19
00:00:58,979 --> 00:01:02,220
<i>their most important lessons
outside the classroom.</i>

20
00:01:03,963 --> 00:01:07,985
<i>They learn to find peaceful
ways to resolve conflict...</i>

21
00:01:09,728 --> 00:01:12,529
<i>to make smart choices about nutrition...</i>

22
00:01:14,070 --> 00:01:17,291
<i>to master the art of conversation.</i>

23
00:01:20,301 --> 00:01:22,405
<i>But for Gabrielle Solis,</i>

24
00:01:22,405 --> 00:01:24,643
<i>the art of morning drop-off...</i>

25
00:01:24,735 --> 00:01:27,628
What's taking so long? Come on! Let's go!

26
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:30,490
<i>Was something she'd never learned.</i>

27
00:01:31,417 --> 00:01:34,117
You slow down, push the kid out,
and drive off!

28
00:01:34,117 --> 00:01:35,933
Why is it so hard?!

29
00:01:36,116 --> 00:01:38,567
You realize I have to go
to this school, right?

30
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:41,660
Oh, come on. I'm behind
the wheelchair kid?

31
00:01:41,660 --> 00:01:42,947
That's it, Juanita. Get out.

32
00:01:42,947 --> 00:01:44,751
I'm not allowed till
we get to the green zone

33
00:01:44,751 --> 00:01:46,323
and a volunteer opens the door.

34
00:01:46,323 --> 00:01:47,699
Remember what happened last week?

35
00:01:47,699 --> 00:01:50,713
Yeah, last week I made it
to my hot stone massage.

36
00:01:50,773 --> 00:01:52,073
Just keep your head down,

37
00:01:52,073 --> 00:01:53,563
pretend like you don't
speak english, and run.

38
