Oh!

66
00:03:20,723 --> 00:03:22,743
You know what, Dana?
Just because you're head of P.T.A.

67
00:03:22,743 --> 00:03:24,405
doesn't mean you get to make the laws!

68
00:03:24,405 --> 00:03:27,782
Oh, I have news for you.
Here at Oakridge, I am the law.

69
00:03:29,060 --> 00:03:32,095
<i>Yes, some of our most important lessons</i>

70
00:03:32,095 --> 00:03:34,560
<i>are learned outside the class room.</i>

71
00:03:34,943 --> 00:03:37,433
<i>And when it came to school politics,</i>

72
00:03:38,119 --> 00:03:42,173
<i>Gabrielle's education was just beginning.</i>

73
00:03:54,538 --> 00:03:56,704
<i>When it came to her separation,</i>

74
00:03:56,704 --> 00:04:01,289
<i>Lynette Scavo was determined
to do everything by the book.</i>

75
00:04:02,574 --> 00:04:04,713
<i>She made sure her visitation days</i>

76
00:04:04,713 --> 00:04:06,602
<i>were evenly divided.</i>

77
00:04:07,826 --> 00:04:11,675
<i>She kept perfect records
of her household expenses.</i>

78
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:16,614
<i>She found healthy ways
to relieve her stress.</i>

79
00:04:18,115 --> 00:04:20,318
<i>Yes, Lynette was confident</i>

80
00:04:20,318 --> 00:04:23,053
<i>her by-the-book approach
was the right one,</i>

81
00:04:23,739 --> 00:04:27,151
<i>sadly, not everyone was on the same page.</i>

82
00:04:27,151 --> 00:04:29,387
Well, look who cleaned
out the sad-sack aisle

83
00:04:29,387 --> 00:04:30,722
at the bookstore.

84
00:04:30,780 --> 00:04:33,124
At least your divorce is good
for the publishing industry.

85
00:04:33,124 --> 00:04:35,152
We're not using the "D" word.

86
00:04:35,152 --> 00:04:36,899
It's a separation.

87
00:04:36,899 --> 00:04:40,694
Tom and I are going to
"Heal through counseling"

88
00:04:40,694 --> 00:04:44,389
so we can find "A road to reconnection"

89
00:04:44,389 --> 00:04:45,960
and if not,

90
00:04:46,445 --> 00:04:48,559
"Murder on the orient express."

91
00:04:51,239 --> 00:04:53,827
Penny, your dad's here!

92
00:04:54,149 --> 00:04:55,364
Explain something to me.

93
00:04:55,364 --> 00:04:56,912
If you're trying to win back your husband,

94
00:04:56,912 --> 00:04:59,522
why do you dress like you
sell oranges by the freeway?

95
00:05:00,172 --> 00:05:02,141
Hey. Sorry I'm late.

96
00:05:02,238 --> 00:05:03,912
I had to stop at the store,

97
00:05:03,913 --> 00:05:05,465
and it took longer than I expected.

98
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:08,295
Because you tawt you taw a puddy tat?

99
00:05:08,693 --> 00:05:10,214
Ha ha.

100
00:05:12,216 --> 00:05:14,058
It's just a teeth whitener.

101
00:05:14,767 --> 00:05:16,079
Teeth whitening, huh?

102
00:05:16,632 --> 00:05:19,007
And unless sweat suits are
the new business casual,

103
00:05:19,007 --> 00:05:21,037
it looks like you're working out, too.

104
00:05:21,514 --> 00:05:25,238
I'm trying. It helps cheer me
up when the kids aren't around.

105
00:05:25,238 --> 00:05:26,753
- Daddy!
- Hey!

106
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:29,170
Oh! Remember to get Parker at practice.

107
00:05:29,170 --> 00:05:31,771
- I love you. Have fun at your dad's.
- I love you. Bye.

108
00:05:31,771 --> 00:05:32,944
Drive safe.

109
00:05:36,407 --> 00:05:37,359
Hmm.

110
00:05:38,751 --> 00:05:40,782
I've got a new book title for you...

111
00:05:41,263 --> 00:05:43,565
"Your husband's banging somebody."

112
00:05:44,499 --> 00:05:45,545
What?

113
00:05:46,105 --> 00:05:48,304
Chapter one... white teeth.

114
00:05:48,304 --> 00:05:50,594
Chapter two... working out.

115
00:05:50,594 --> 00:05:53,032
Chapter three... the nasty.

116
00:05:53,594 --> 00:05:56,876
He's just trying to take
better care of himself.

117
00:05:56,876 --> 00:05:58,182
Oh, Lynette.

118
00:05:58,182 --> 00:06:01,179
I expect you to be naive about hair,
makeup, and fashion,

119
00:06:01,179 --> 00:06:02,427
but about this?

120
00:06:02,543 --> 00:06:05,313
Trust me. Tom has hooked up.

121
00:06:05,313 --> 00:06:07,852
He's not. He's not. If he was...

122
00:06:07,925 --> 00:06:09,606
dating someone,

123
00:06:09,606 --> 00:06:10,968
he would tell me.

124
00:06:13,325 --> 00:06:14,331
He would.

125
00:06:16,697 --> 00:06:17,578
Right?

126
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:39,043
- That doesn't look too suspicious.
- Oh.

127
00:06:40,078 --> 00:06:41,969
I'm sorry. Just...
every time I check the mail,

128
00:06:41,969 --> 00:06:44,208
I'm afraid it's gonna be
another one of those letters.

129
00:06:44,313 --> 00:06:46,663
It's been three weeks.
Maybe we're out of the woods.

130
00:06:46,826 --> 00:06:47,986
Please don't say "Woods."

131
00:06:47,986 --> 00:06:50,185
I'm just saying, if someone
was trying to blackmail us,

132
00:06:50,185 --> 00:06:51,481
they're not very good at it,

133
00:06:51,481 --> 00:06:53,248
since they haven't asked
for money or anything.

134
00:06:53,248 --> 00:06:56,330
Well, what happened to them?
Did they just disappear?

135
00:06:56,554 --> 00:06:57,677
If we're lucky.

136
00:06:58,113 --> 00:07:00,216
Now that Chuck the cop
is out of your life,

137
00:07:00,216 --> 00:07:01,545
Susan's acting normal,

138
00:07:01,545 --> 00:07:02,975
I think we're in the clear.

139
00:07:04,552 --> 00:07:06,976
Oh, good. Here they are. Hmm.

140
00:07:07,882 --> 00:07:10,114
Oh, Danielle and Benjamin.

141
00:07:10,832 --> 00:07:12,322
Fun. What's the occasion?

142
00:07:12,365 --> 00:07:13,803
Her husband left her.

143
00:07:13,803 --> 00:07:16,057
Ugh. Okay. Well, I'd stay and say hi,

144
00:07:16,057 --> 00:07:18,595
but that would involve a lot
of listening and sad nodding.

145
00:07:21,318 --> 00:07:24,048
Oh, honey, I am so sorry
about you and Leo.

146
00:07:24,048 --> 00:07:24,966
Thanks, mom.

147
00:07:24,966 --> 00:07:26,719
Not that I didn't see it coming.

148
00:07:27,503 --> 00:07:28,646
That didn't take long.

149
00:07:28,646 --> 00:07:30,218
Neither did the marriage.

150
00:07:31,017 --> 00:07:32,464
So how are you holding up?

151
00:07:32,464 --> 00:07:34,487
My husband left me. It sucks.

152
00:07:35,324 --> 00:07:36,908
But you know how that feels.

153
00:07:37,685 --> 00:07:39,978
You just got dumped by that cop, right?

154
00:07:40,561 --> 00:07:41,731
Um...

155
00:07:42,129 --> 00:07:44,792
Actually, I am the one
who ended it with Chuck.

156
00:07:44,792 --> 00:07:47,285
He wanted to marry me, bought me a ring,

157
00:07:47,511 --> 00:07:49,704
but that's not important.

158
00:07:49,704 --> 00:07:51,198
This week...

159
00:07:53,232 --> 00:07:55,149
or weeks is about you.

160
00:07:55,149 --> 00:07:57,692
We are gonna make a plan to
put your life back together.

161
00:07:57,692 --> 00:07:59,994
A plan? Mom, this all just happened.

162
00:08:00,253 --> 00:08:03,590
Give me a few days to eat
ice cream and veg out.

163
00:08:03,694 --> 00:08:06,523
Of course, honey.
I promised you on your wedding day

164
00:08:06,523 --> 00:08:08,731
that I would be here when he left you.

165
00:08:10,589 --> 00:08:11,466
You know what?

166
00:08:11,466 --> 00:08:13,521
Maybe we'll just crash on Andrew's floor.

167
00:08:13,521 --> 00:08:15,564
What? That's so uncomfortable.

168
00:08:15,564 --> 00:08:18,790
Not as bad as staying here and
getting picked apart by you.

169
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:22,039
I promise I won't criticize you.

170
00:08:23,148 --> 00:08:24,725
Besides, if you sleep on Andrew's floor,

171
00:08:24,725 --> 00:08:26,250
you'll need a tetanus shot.

172
00:08:27,936 --> 00:08:29,711
What? I said I wouldn't criticize you.

173
00:08:29,711 --> 00:08:31,617
I didn't say anything about your brother.

174
00:08:44,970 --> 00:08:46,263
Okay, I know that last night

175
00:08:46,263 --> 00:08:47,907
I said you could take
all the time you need

176
00:08:47,907 --> 00:08:50,229
to work through what
Carlos and I told you,

177
00:08:50,229 --> 00:08:51,139
but...

178
00:08:51,946 --> 00:08:54,114
while you're taking all the time you need,

179
00:08:54,763 --> 00:08:56,200
you think you could maybe...

180
00:08:57,274 --> 00:08:59,122
tell me that you still love me?

181
00:08:59,856 --> 00:09:00,899
I mean...

182
00:09:01,563 --> 00:09:02,837
if you still love me?

183
00:09:07,411 --> 00:09:09,217
There is nothing you could do

184
00:09:10,192 --> 00:09:11,891
that would make me stop loving you.

185
00:09:13,391 --> 00:09:17,405
Mike, it was so hard
to keep this from you,

186
00:09:17,405 --> 00:09:19,241
like, the hardest thing I've ever done.

187
00:09:19,638 --> 00:09:22,906
Well, at least I understand
why you've been so distant.

188
00:09:23,990 --> 00:09:25,081
And to be honest,

189
00:09:25,081 --> 00:09:26,937
I'm kind of relieved you
weren't having an affair.

190
00:09:27,568 --> 00:09:29,065
Well, now that you know,

191
00:09:29,328 --> 00:09:31,344
I just want everything
to go back to normal.

192
00:09:34,370 --> 00:09:36,947
Okay, but I hope you realize

193
00:09:36,947 --> 00:09:38,262
it might not be that easy.

194
00:09:40,346 --> 00:09:43,765
Take it from a guy who's
done things like this.

195
00:09:43,765 --> 00:09:45,176
They don't just disappear.

196
00:09:47,035 --> 00:09:48,288
Yeah, I know that.

197
00:09:49,636 --> 00:09:52,626
But I think if I focus on other stuff

198
00:09:53,061 --> 00:09:54,768
and move on with my life,

199
00:09:54,778 --> 00:09:56,032
it'll be okay.

200
00:09:56,574 --> 00:09:57,606
Great.

201
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:01,078
And first step?

202
00:10:02,003 --> 00:10:04,094
I'm taking a painting
class at the college.

203
00:10:04,168 --> 00:10:06,447
It's being taught by Andre Zeller.

204
00:10:08,318 --> 00:10:10,064
Okay, that means nothing to you.

205
00:10:10,455 --> 00:10:12,905
It's like I'm taking a football class

206
00:10:12,905 --> 00:10:14,496
from Peyton Manning.

207
00:10:14,496 --> 00:10:15,589
Whoa.

208
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:18,313
It's just what I need.

209
00:10:18,423 --> 00:10:19,644
I think it'll be a great way

210
00:10:19,644 --> 00:10:21,579
to take my mind off
everything that's happened.

211
00:10:22,417 --> 00:10:24,904
So I'm gonna get my portfolio together.

212
00:10:24,904 --> 00:10:27,287
Mr. Zeller has to approve
all his students.

213
00:10:27,287 --> 00:10:28,613
Not that I'm worried.

214
00:10:29,392 --> 00:10:30,689
Oh, and, Mike,

215
00:10:31,185 --> 00:10:33,401
from now on, I swear,

216
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:36,064
no more secrets between us.

217
00:10:45,199 --> 00:10:46,406
Is that my school?

218
00:10:46,406 --> 00:10:48,549
The tiny, little building way down there?

219
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:50,872
It would've been faster
if we just walked from home.

220
00:10:52,028 --> 00:10:53,004
Hey.

221
00:10:53,385 --> 00:10:55,019
First time in the "B" lot, huh?

222
00:10:56,664 --> 00:10:58,576
- Welcome.
- What are you in for?

223
00:10:59,037 --> 00:11:00,066
Practically nothing.

224
00:11:00,066 --> 00:11:02,053
I let my kid get out
of the car by herself.

225
00:11:02,085 --> 00:11:04,775
- Ooh.
- Dana take your placard?

226
00:11:04,775 --> 00:11:07,685
Yeah, but I'll get it
back in a day or two.

227
00:11:09,335 --> 00:11:10,393
Are you kidding?

228
00:11:10,393 --> 00:11:12,430
She'll have you in here
for the rest of the year.

229
00:11:12,430 --> 00:11:14,613
What? She can't do that.

230
00:11:14,613 --> 00:11:15,822
Oh, you wanna bet?

231
00:11:15,822 --> 00:11:18,587
I took a cell phone
call in the green zone.

232
00:11:18,986 --> 00:11:20,337
That was two months ago.

233
00:11:20,337 --> 00:11:23,514
My kid had peanut butter
crackers in his lunchbox.

234
00:11:23,514 --> 00:11:25,178
I'm looking at four to six.

235
00:11:25,178 --> 00:11:26,624
This is crazy.

236
00:11:26,624 --> 00:11:28,464
No, this is Dana.

237
00:11:28,464 --> 00:11:30,169
Dana "The pain-a." Pfft!

238
00:11:30,169 --> 00:11:32,083
Dana "You better not complain-a."

239
00:11:32,494 --> 00:11:34,565
Dana "Power's driving me insane-a."

240
00:11:35,546 --> 00:11:37,712
Oh, my god. Is this what
the "B" lot does to you?

241
00:11:37,712 --> 00:11:40,782
That, four kids,
and the flask in her purse.

242
00:11:40,792 --> 00:11:43,584
Well, if everyone thinks
she's such a pain-a,

243
00:11:43,584 --> 00:11:44,700
how'd she get the job?

244
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:47,607
It's an elected position.
We voted for her.

245
00:11:47,607 --> 00:11:50,006
Well, not me. I don't vote.

246
00:11:50,673 --> 00:11:52,661
All right, when's the next P.T.A. meeting?

247
00:11:52,727 --> 00:11:54,055
There's one thursday.

248
00:11:54,055 --> 00:11:57,307
Okay. I say we band together,

249
00:11:57,434 --> 00:12:00,570
storm that meeting, and go all
"Braveheart" on Dana's ass.

250
00:12:00,570 --> 00:12:01,796
Who's with me?

251
00:12:04,151 --> 00:12:05,604
You guys not seen "Braveheart"?

252
00:12:06,049 --> 00:12:09,085
I know it's an old reference,
but this is when you go, "Yeah!"

253
00:12:09,568 --> 00:12:11,197
Yeah.

254
00:12:11,334 --> 00:12:12,865
Oh, god. Come on.

255
00:12:12,865 --> 00:12:15,431
If every fed-up mom in
